wikipedia_page.main: Lucy Cane CBE (c.1866 – 23 April 1926) was an Irish public servant.

response: In 1909 Furse joined the British Red Cross Voluntary Aid Detachment attached to the Territorial Army. In 1911, she was lodging with Lucy Cane and family at 66 Elm Park Gardens, Chelsea.
* Lucy Cane, Irish public servant, also known as Mary Cane
